Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.27,0:00:02.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Love and hate are brought together...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.90,0:00:04.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Through both reasoning and suspense!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.82,0:00:06.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the first Detective Boys episode in a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.53,0:00:08.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko's acting kind of strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.41,0:00:09.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing through to the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.91,0:00:11.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I look like a child, but have the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.78,0:00:13.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.96,0:01:49.92,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,First, let's raise our arms way up high and stretch our backs!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.92,0:01:51.26,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.26,0:01:54.59,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,One,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.01,0:01:56.22,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Five,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.22,0:01:57.10,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Five, six.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.10,0:01:58.26,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Now, move them in a swinging motion!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.89,0:01:59.85,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,One,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.85,0:02:00.68,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,One, two,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.68,0:02:01.60,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,One, two, three...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.60,0:02:02.52,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Four,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.52,0:02:04.27,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Four, five,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.27,0:02:05.27,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Four, five, six, seven,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.27,0:02:05.86,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Four, five, six, seven, eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.77,0:02:06.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.86,0:02:06.94,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,One,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.82,0:02:11.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really can't believe we're spending summer vacation doing these exercises with the 5th graders...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.94,0:02:08.02,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,One, two,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.02,0:02:08.90,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,One, two, three,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.90,0:02:09.65,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,One, two, three, four...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.65,0:02:10.32,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Five,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.32,0:02:11.15,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Five, six.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.24,0:02:12.36,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Arms in circles!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.36,0:02:14.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What am I doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.86,0:02:13.65,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Keep going!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.53,0:02:15.49,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,You're doing great!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.58,0:02:17.58,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Five,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.58,0:02:18.41,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Five, six,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.41,0:02:19.37,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Five, six, seven,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.37,0:02:19.79,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Five, six, seven, eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.75,0:02:23.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko's Mystifying Forest:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.62,0:02:24.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Part 1!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.79,0:02:28.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.21,0:02:33.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan. Do it properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.84,0:02:39.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Radio exercising is an important symbol of summer, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.14,0:02:40.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Symbol of summer, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.93,0:02:42.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.48,0:02:47.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you don't exercise properly, you'll regret it when you're older.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.02,0:02:51.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,High blood pressure, diabetes, high cholesterol.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.19,0:02:56.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You could even get cardiovascular disorders or ischemic heart disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.87,0:03:01.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One, two, three, four!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.83,0:03:05.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it's true that it will be good for the Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.67,0:03:11.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this about a "newspaper of summer"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.76,0:03:14.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The symbol of summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.05,0:03:16.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It makes you feel like summer is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.64,0:03:20.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you remember the professor talking about it on our way home from the fireworks?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.39,0:03:25.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There aren't that many symbols of summer in the city anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.89,0:03:30.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fireworks and radio exercising are some of the few symbols that haven't disappeared over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.73,0:03:32.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of disappearing...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.86,0:03:36.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsuburaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} isn't here today, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.24,0:03:39.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder what happened to Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.16,0:03:42.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He hasn't come for the past few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.04,0:03:44.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably overslept and decided to ditch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.91,0:03:46.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.92,0:03:51.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unlike Genta, who's loose about time, Mitsuhiko is the type who always comes early.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.67,0:03:52.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.55,0:03:53.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Loose?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.26,0:03:56.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How am I wrinkly?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.88,0:03:59.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those are loose socks!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.51,0:04:03.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why don't we all go to Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s house later to check on him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.89,0:04:07.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He might have a summer cold or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.69,0:04:09.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, let's do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.28,0:04:17.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Mit{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} didn't go?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.45,0:04:19.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's weird...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.87,0:04:23.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he was going camping with everyone after radio exercising.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.74,0:04:25.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Camping?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.08,0:04:29.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. He was packing up last night, and seemed really excited about going.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.13,0:04:35.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was putting some sasa-dango in his backpack, and was planning to share it with everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.88,0:04:35.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: Sasa-dango is a Japanese rice cake wrapped in bamboo leaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.13,0:04:37.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sasa-dango?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.80,0:04:42.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! A kind lady next door gave us a whole bunch!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.10,0:04:44.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I guess you aren't going camping?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.06,0:04:47.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Well, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.56,0:04:51.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you're Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s sister, do you have any idea where he might be?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.61,0:04:54.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Any secret hiding places or any place like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.82,0:04:59.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know. Mit{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} is usually hanging out with you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.32,0:05:00.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.82,0:05:03.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you want to look inside Mit{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s room?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.33,0:05:06.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He usually leaves a note there when he goes somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.91,0:05:08.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.54,0:05:11.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.17,0:05:16.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess he didn't leave a note, after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.09,0:05:19.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His wallet is missing, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.59,0:05:20.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His wallet?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.63,0:05:25.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he brought a day's worth of food and his wallet, that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.26,0:05:27.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must have gone somewhere far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.43,0:05:30.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, you aren't suggesting...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.48,0:05:32.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a possibility that he ran away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.48,0:05:34.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran away!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.48,0:05:36.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh, oh my gosh, seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.32,0:05:37.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is just like a TV drama!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.07,0:05:40.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you so happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.03,0:05:45.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, even if he didn't run away, he was definitely planning something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.74,0:05:52.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look. Mitsuhiko's radio exercise stamp card shows he only skipped on Sundays.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.25,0:05:56.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.71,0:06:00.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does he have something to do on sunday?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.17,0:06:02.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he's going on a date with someone!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.26,0:06:04.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.34,0:06:06.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Date?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.43,0:06:09.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, Mit{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} talked about some older girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.52,0:06:14.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She helps out in her parents' flower shop on Sundays.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.60,0:06:18.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I remember him telling me that middle-school girl said he was "very cool."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.03,0:06:24.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that she invited Mit{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} to go to the beach with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.28,0:06:25.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why the beach?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.16,0:06:30.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he was packing last night, he came and asked to borrow my sunscreen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.83,0:06:33.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went online and ordered this awesome sunscreen from overseas!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.75,0:06:35.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.96,0:06:37.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} that we know...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.84,0:06:39.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With a girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.84,0:06:41.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the beach?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.84,0:06:43.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eating sasa-dango.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.84,0:06:45.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.97,0:06:48.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, may a have a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.97,0:06:51.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you don't hurry, you'll miss your piano lesson!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.39,0:06:53.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be right there, Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.81,0:06:57.44,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: She addresses her mother politely as "Okaa{\rHonorifics - Signs}-sama{\r}" instead of the usual "Okaa{\rHonorifics - Signs}-san{\r}."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.98,0:06:58.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My parents are both school teachers, so they're really strict about speaking politely.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.11,0:07:02.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No wonder Mitsuhiko always acts so formally.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.40,0:07:07.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, if you get any juicy information, call me on my cell phone, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.24,0:07:09.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want to know about Mit{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s love life too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.91,0:07:18.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her brother is missing, yet she doesn't seem to be worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.46,0:07:19.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kind of unusual, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.71,0:07:21.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.84,0:07:23.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Mitsuhiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.34,0:07:28.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! You mean that Tsuburaya Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.14,0:07:29.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't come today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.97,0:07:32.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not even at 6:30 in the morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.22,0:07:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This shop opens at 7:00 AM, and I was radio exercising at that time, so I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.44,0:07:39.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.48,0:07:46.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I saw him standing at a bus stop last Sunday on my way to radio exercising.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.15,0:07:49.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some old guys were yelling at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.45,0:07:51.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yelling at him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.24,0:07:56.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. They were saying things like\N"I can't tell you," and "you can't have it."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.87,0:07:59.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did they mean by that?\NCan't have what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.50,0:08:01.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.50,0:08:04.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was saying the names of some ancient warlords.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.92,0:08:06.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.42,0:08:08.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uesugi and Takeda?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.01,0:08:09.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.26,0:08:12.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it Toyotomi and Tokugawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.35,0:08:14.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Tokugawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.93,0:08:17.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that he found Tokugawa's buried treasure?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.56,0:08:20.15,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: They are referring to an urban myth about members of the Tokugawa Shogunate burying many historical Shogun-ora artifacts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.94,0:08:21.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's probably hidden at some beach!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.36,0:08:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} went to look for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.15,0:08:25.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Darn that Mitsuhiko! He should've invited us!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.15,0:08:26.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, it's starting all over again...\NDarn that Mitsuhiko! He should've invited us!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.78,0:08:28.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Darn that Mitsuhiko! He should've invited us!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.11,0:08:31.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is Tsuburaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.99,0:08:35.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. He seems to have gone somewhere this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.00,0:08:39.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then maybe that kid I saw this morning was him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.63,0:08:43.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw a boy at the bus stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.42,0:08:47.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A hat was covering his face and he was carrying a backpack.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.34,0:08:50.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He smelled strange for a boy, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.43,0:08:54.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He looked like Tsuburaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, so I called out to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.51,0:08:56.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he ignored me and got on the bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.39,0:09:00.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A strange smell? What did he smell like?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.35,0:09:01.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it wasn't exactly strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.56,0:09:05.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure it was a lemon citrus smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.86,0:09:07.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A lemon smell?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.78,0:09:10.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, I remember him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.74,0:09:14.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The boy with the hat that smelled like lemons, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.45,0:09:17.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was he a runaway, as I thought?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.54,0:09:19.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, no, we're not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.87,0:09:25.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Usually, kids like to look out the bus windows to view the scenery.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.92,0:09:31.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that boy just sat at the back of the bus and stared straight forward with a serious face.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.51,0:09:35.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He seemed scared and acted like he was hiding from something.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.35,0:09:37.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A serious face?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.56,0:09:39.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiding from something?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.27,0:09:44.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He ran away! Mitsuhiko really did run away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.15,0:09:45.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.23,0:09:48.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, do you know where he got off?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.49,0:09:51.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm, I think it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.15,0:09:53.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beika Station?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.70,0:09:58.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A boy that smelled like lemons?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.95,0:10:00.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was there a kid like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.91,0:10:04.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was wearing a hat and had a backpack on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.00,0:10:08.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, could you be asking about that one kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.51,0:10:11.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, the one who bought an adult ticket by mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.18,0:10:15.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, the one who was in a hurry to change tickets.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.85,0:10:17.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was in a hurry?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.22,0:10:22.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was almost like he was being chased by someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.48,0:10:26.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know which train he got on, or where he went?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.90,0:10:29.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.44,0:10:32.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was 1900 yen ($21 USD) for an adult ticket...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.65,0:10:35.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only places that would cost that much are the Chiba Prefecture...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.74,0:10:38.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or even the Gunma Prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.21,0:10:45.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.92,0:10:48.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,None of the station workers saw him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.59,0:10:52.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that means he's probably transferred trains already.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.10,0:11:05.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is this train's last stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.73,0:11:10.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he was here
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.48,0:11:11.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.61,0:11:12.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.78,0:11:17.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unlike the city, we don't have automated ticket barriers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.62,0:11:22.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since we have to check each one by hand, I wouldn't forget a boy like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.20,0:11:26.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He got off last and seemed to be hiding from something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.50,0:11:29.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looked like he was headed towards the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.84,0:11:33.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.01,0:11:39.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the information about the scent of lemons, the hat, and the backpack, we made it to the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.60,0:11:42.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sun's starting to set.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.97,0:11:45.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.77,0:11:47.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing here...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.98,0:11:49.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How are we going to find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.40,0:11:52.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.99,0:11:57.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? Mitsuhiko's detective badge is responding.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.78,0:11:59.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's definitely somewhere in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.16,0:12:02.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.41,0:12:07.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on... If Mitsuhiko has his badge, why don't you call him?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.63,0:12:12.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been trying, but he's not responding.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.21,0:12:19.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, with these glasses we should be able to find him soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.55,0:12:21.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But doesn't it make you wonder?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.31,0:12:27.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it that made Tsuburaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, the serious and considerate one...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.06,0:12:33.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...turn his back on us for the first time and travel this far into the mountains?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.48,0:12:36.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Do you think he really ran away?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.36,0:12:40.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now, cheer up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.03,0:12:42.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's probably got a good reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.53,0:12:46.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he fell in love with a girl he saw and chased her here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.50,0:12:48.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Love can make a person do some crazy things.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.46,0:12:50.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fell in love?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.96,0:12:53.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know what they say...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.30,0:12:55.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"First love tastes like lemons!"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.88,0:12:59.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go, guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.13,0:13:01.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We need to find him before it gets dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.43,0:13:02.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.16,0:13:29.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like he's somewhere in this forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.66,0:13:32.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And? You still can't get in contact with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.96,0:13:34.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.13,0:13:37.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko's probably not answering because he hears the tracker's beeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.38,0:13:43.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, there's a big crowd of people over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.89,0:13:48.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, let's ask if they saw Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.14,0:13:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait here. I'll go ask them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.85,0:13:51.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone stay here and—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.15,0:13:53.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.48,0:13:57.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't know if they are dangerous or not!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.07,0:14:02.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! You bunch of old guys over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.91,0:14:11.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officer Yamamura from the Gunma Police...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.67,0:14:15.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? Aren't you the kid who's always with Detective Mouri?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.63,0:14:18.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing all the way out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.55,0:14:21.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What, you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.30,0:14:24.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.60,0:14:27.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No time for small talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.35,0:14:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This place is dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.06,0:14:37.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to ask you to leave this place immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.44,0:14:41.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dangerous? Are there bears around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.32,0:14:45.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A man way more scary than a bear is hiding in this forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.28,0:14:47.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A man?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.45,0:14:49.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.29,0:14:51.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I don't want him to hear me say this...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.71,0:14:55.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But one of the elder officers wasn't paying attention, and let him escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.17,0:14:59.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The serial killer, Numabuchi Kiichiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.96,0:15:02.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What?>
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.80,0:15:05.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.68,0:15:10.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come now, and no sudden moves.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.27,0:15:16.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.86,0:15:21.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.28,0:15:24.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.28,0:15:27.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get the hell out of my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.46,0:15:41.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The guy I met in Osaka is in this forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.46,0:15:43.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you need to leave quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.59,0:15:45.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But in this forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.64,0:15:48.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.60,0:15:51.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have to hurry and tell Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} about this, or else...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.52,0:15:56.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it! Why aren't you answering, Mitsuhiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.37,0:16:19.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A child is in this forest!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.17,0:16:23.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this forest, where there's a murderer on the loose?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.51,0:16:24.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.84,0:16:27.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you keep an eye on him?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.01,0:16:29.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You brought him here, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.30,0:16:31.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I didn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.97,0:16:36.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko came here on his own without even telling us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.48,0:16:41.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, we got a whole bunch of information from the train station workers that led us here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.40,0:16:49.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We ended up in this forest, thanks to the transmitter in his Detective Badge showing his location.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.03,0:16:51.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I used my Tracking Glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.37,0:16:54.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A "Detective Badge"...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.12,0:16:56.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And "Tracking Glasses"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.25,0:17:01.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I was a kid, my parents bought me gimmicky little detective toys like that too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.46,0:17:07.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like a magic invisible ink pen and a magical playing card that turns into smoke when you rub it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.22,0:17:10.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And a memopad that melts in water.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.55,0:17:14.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But one day, I asked myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.43,0:17:17.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do these gimmicks help investigations in real life?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.98,0:17:18.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.02,0:17:26.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now then, if your information concerning the whereabouts of that boy is based on some silly detective toys...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.99,0:17:28.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go play somewhere else!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.74,0:17:32.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, no, those aren't toys...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.12,0:17:33.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're really for real!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.70,0:17:37.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're absolutely sure Mitsuhiko is in this forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.37,0:17:41.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fine, then show them to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.00,0:17:43.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These so-called "Tracking Glasses" of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.92,0:17:47.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? All you have to do is press this button on the rim.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.13,0:17:52.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crap! Out of batteries?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.64,0:17:55.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Told you so!\NThey look like an ordinary pair of glasses to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.76,0:17:58.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, it's out of batteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.77,0:17:59.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.39,0:18:02.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Yamamura! What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.10,0:18:04.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C'mon, we gotta find Numabuchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.48,0:18:07.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But these children...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.44,0:18:11.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's your fault Numabuchi got away!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.07,0:18:12.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So take this seriously, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.91,0:18:14.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, actually it was you who...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.83,0:18:21.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, take the children to a safe place and then come back to help look for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.29,0:18:23.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.92,0:18:27.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honestly now...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.46,0:18:32.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murderer got away because Senpai had to pee and left his post.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.76,0:18:37.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought he was next to me, so I wasn't paying attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.93,0:18:42.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it was your fault, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.06,0:18:46.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-If you want to put it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.98,0:18:49.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.28,0:18:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.15,0:18:53.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.91,0:18:56.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop hiding and come out
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.78,0:18:58.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.79,0:19:01.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How much longer do you intend to scream your lungs out?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.12,0:19:03.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet that boy already went home.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.04,0:19:06.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should go home, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.50,0:19:10.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it gets any darker, you'll get lost even if you know this place well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.51,0:19:12.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're not scared of the dark!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.51,0:19:14.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have these!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.01,0:19:18.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He, they sell really convenient things these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.39,0:19:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We didn't buy these.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.97,0:19:22.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Professor made them for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.02,0:19:24.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Professor? Made them?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.48,0:19:29.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I invented them for the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.02,0:19:35.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Along with the Detective Badges and Tracking Glasses that we were talking about earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.41,0:19:37.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-So, wait a second...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.82,0:19:42.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be... that you were telling the truth about a child being lost in this forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.50,0:19:46.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course it's true.\NThat's what we've been trying to tell you all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.17,0:19:50.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, why didn't you tell one of the elder officers?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.42,0:19:52.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.76,0:19:56.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I have to inform Senpai of this immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.47,0:20:03.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shoot! I left my cell phone back in the patrol car!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.64,0:20:05.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm a failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.60,0:20:09.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, I let a criminal escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.44,0:20:14.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I fail to tell the others about a lost boy. I'm gonna lose my job for sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.78,0:20:18.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted to be a policeman ever since I saw a police drama on TV when I was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.82,0:20:25.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that my dreams have finally come true, I guess I'm not fit for this role...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.62,0:20:27.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As an officer...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.92,0:20:29.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.00,0:20:33.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's okay, you don't have to try to comfort me...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.51,0:20:37.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Officer{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you've solved so many cases before!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.68,0:20:39.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The case with Yabuuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.93,0:20:42.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The case with the lawyers in Karuizawa...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.60,0:20:45.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the one in the Kashiragami forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.73,0:20:48.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've helped everyone so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.02,0:20:49.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true, Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.86,0:20:51.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.40,0:20:52.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.69,0:20:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it was actually my dad or I who solved those cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.36,0:21:02.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that I think about it, your wide forehead even makes you look really smart!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.08,0:21:04.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the epitome of an intelligent policeman.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.62,0:21:06.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.71,0:21:13.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officer Yamamura, cheer up and let's look for him. We'll rely on you since you're familiar with this forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.30,0:21:16.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, Agasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.26,0:21:19.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From now on...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.43,0:21:21.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please call me Yama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.26,0:21:23.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.51,0:21:27.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's definitely watched too many police dramas.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.82,0:21:43.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's beeping again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.58,0:21:45.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must be Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.45,0:21:48.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and the others came to look for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.08,0:21:54.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if I answer the badge now, this whole trip would become a waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.09,0:22:02.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. I definitely won't let that happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.74,0:23:50.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a chance that Numabuchi Kiichiro has already killed him...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.37,0:23:51.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.04,0:23:52.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.41,0:23:54.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, isn't it possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.25,0:24:00.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, he committed three murders in three consecutive days.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.59,0:24:02.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.26,0:24:03.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.88,0:24:06.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you can hear my voice, answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.01,0:24:08.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This forest is dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.85,0:24:11.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a serial killer on the loose!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.89,0:24:15.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan: Mitsuhiko's Mystifying Forest, Part 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.82,0:24:26.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please look forward to the next episode!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.82,0:24:25.19,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,When are you coming back, Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.20,0:24:26.82,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Think about your situation a little, Tsubura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
